\N<Naoto>Oh, right, haha. Grandma was out, wasn't she?
\N<Kaede>Yeah. So I said welcome back instead, haha.
\N<Kaede>Hmm, I'm hungry. Well then, I'll make dinner today.

\N<Naoto>Yes! Kaede's cooking is several times more delicious than
mine, isn't it?! ♪
\N<Kaede>U-um, I feel like I'm being stared at... haha.

\N<Kaede>If you keep staring at me like that, of course I'll notice...
haha.
\N<Kaede>I already told you to drop that topic, didn't I?
\N<Kaede>Yeah, I've been through a lot of tough things....

\N<Kaede>Right now, just being able to eat together with Naoto and do
work in the fields, and being able to sleep together, that's enough
for me.

\N<Kaede>Alright, it's done...! Well then, go ahead. I'm going to take
a bath.
\N<Naoto>Well then, should I take a bath now-!
\N<Kaede>Huh? You don't have to go to Tanaka-san's house?
\N<Kaede>Okay. Well then, I'll go take a bath first!
\N<Naoto> Alright, let's do our best with the field work today.
\N<Naoto>Ah, coming back home always feels so calming.
\N<Kaede>Are you okay? Did you drink too much?
\N<Naoto>By the way, Kaede really does hate Miya-kun, huh?

\N<Kaede>Yeah... Because that guy's words and actions are always so
thoughtless, you know?

\N<Naoto>Ah, yeah. Kaede really does hate that kind of thing, huh?
Haha.
\N<Kaede>And one thing that bothers me is,
\N<Kaede>I wonder why he came back to the village.
\N<Naoto>Did he say he missed this village or something?
\N<Kaede>It just doesn't sit right with me.
\N<Kaede>Hmm, something doesn't sit right with me....

\N<Naoto>Well, there's no point in worrying too much about it! It's
already late, so let's go to sleep today!
\N<Naoto>Phew, it's good that everything has been resolved....

\N<Naoto>Even though I was told such things.... I couldn't say
anything back....

\N<Naoto>At this point, I'll say it clearly. I'm no longer concerned
about Aya.

\N<Naoto>And besides, I've met someone who I can cherish so much right
now. So, it's okay.
\N<Naoto>Anyway, I'm really looking forward to tomorrow's barbecue!

\N<Naoto>Of course! It would be a waste not to swim in such a
beautiful sea during the barbecue!
\N<Naoto>Ah, you're embarrassed to wear a swimsuit, aren't you? Haha.

\N<Naoto>Well, it seems like Tanaka-san and everyone else will be
coming! If everyone is going to swim, Kaede, you should also wear a
swimsuit!
\N<Kaede>Um, do you...want to see me in a swimsuit?
\N<Naoto>Of course I want to see you in a swimsuit! Haha.

\N<Naoto>Besides, it would be tough if we don't cool off even a little
bit under the scorching sun, haha.
\N<Naoto>Alright! Let's get some rest to prepare for tomorrow!!

\N<Kaede>What is it? If you have something to say, go ahead and say
it.

\N<Kaede>Well, it's more like he accidentally bumped into me rather
than saying he touched me...

\N<Naoto>Ah, no... That's not it...! It's not like I want you to
apologize or anything...
\N<Kaede>But... you didn't like it, right... I'm sorry.
\N<Kaede>I don't think... anything like that happened....
\N<Naoto>Ah, don't apologize...!! I-I don't mind, so...!!
\N<Naoto>Yeah, I'm fine. Ah...you should go take a bath...!
\N<Kaede>Okay, I got it. I'll go take a bath.
\N<Naoto>Welcome back! I did well today! Are you hungry?
\N<Kaede>The other person... is quite mysterious, aren't they...
\N<Kaede>If you're okay with that... then it's fine...
\N<Kaede>Where do you plan to be at that time, Naoto...
\N<Kaede>You don't plan on being nearby, do you...?
\N<Naoto>So, it's not okay to watch it outside... I guess...
\N<Naoto>No, it's... I'm sorry for being unreasonable.

\N<Kaede>I'm only doing this to help Naoto recover. Once he's healed,
I won't do it anymore.
\N<Naoto>L-Let's go talk to Miya-kun right away...!!

\N<Naoto>Please... let's continue the conversation... I can't calm
down... I won't be able to sleep....
\N<Kaede>You, you mustn't come to see me... so, okay?
\N<Naoto>It... It's been quite a while, hasn't it....
\N<Kaede>Y-Yeah.... I did it with my hands....
\N<Naoto>Ah, ah... It's... erect... It hurts so much...
\N<Naoto>W-Would you... do it now... the same way...

\N<Naoto>Ah, um... It means drawing a lottery and doing what is
written on it...
\N<Kaede>Does that mean... we have to go beyond just drawing?

\N<Kaede>So... Naoto, you're the one who comes up with the contents of
the lottery, right?

\N<Kaede>So... Naoto, it means that there's something you want me to
do, right?
\N<Kaede>Ah..... I get it. Well, that's fine then.
\N<Kaede>I... I did it.... The thing Naoto wanted me to do....
\N<Kaede>It'll be ready soon, so please wait.

\N<Kaede>Oh, come to think of it, weren't we supposed to go to the
village chief's house today?

\N<Naoto>Oh...! Are you talking about the village revitalization
project?

\N<Kaede>Every year, it seemed like such a difficult task, but it has
finally come around to us...

\N<Naoto>I can't think of any ideas for revitalizing the village...
I'm at a loss...
\N<Kaede>Do we really need to think so hard about it?

\N<Naoto>Alright. Let's stop by the village chief's house before going
to the fields!
\N<Naoto>I feel like I slept more peacefully than usual.
\N<Naoto>Alright, let's do our best with the field work today!
\N<Kaede>Yeah. It's getting hot, so let's make sure to stay hydrated.
\N<Naoto>Ah-.... um... it's about the village revitalization plan....
\N<Naoto>Huh... Ah, it's better not to overthink it....
\N<Naoto>Well, then I'm going to take a bath.
\N<Kaede>I'm going to take a bath too.
\N<Kaede>Strange thing... So, was that a lie...?
\N<Naoto>But, there might be other ways to heal... um...

\N<Naoto>Anyway, let's forget about yesterday's conversation for
now... Just forget it...!
\N<Naoto>Well, then I'll go to the field first...!
\N<Naoto>Shall we go to the field then?
\N<Kaede>No, it's just that I feel comfortable with you, Naoto...
\N<Naoto>Yeah, you're right.... I finally did it...
\N<Naoto>I don't know. Well... maybe... I wonder if it's healed...?
\N<Kaede>So, does that mean it's all over between us, Naoto?
\N<Naoto>Yeah. Then let's go to the field soon...!
\N<Kaede>Ah, welcome back Naoto. It'll be done soon, so please wait.
\N<Kaede>We met...? At the foot of the mountain....
\N<Kaede>I'll be fine tonight. I'm going now.

\N<Kaede>If something strange happens, I'll beat them up without
holding back.

\N<Kaede>Because it might still be impossible if we meet in person.
Don't get your hopes up.
\N<Kaede>Yeah. But I think I'll be back soon.
\N<Naoto>I'll be back soon... W-What do you mean by that....
\N<Kaede>If we do this.... we'll be together again, Naoto....
\N<Naoto>Is she still not here... Kaede... Kaede...
\N<Kaede>The contents of the lottery were written by Naoto, right...?
\N<Naoto>Is it, is it still not here...
\N<Naoto>Wh-What are you doing right now, Kaede...
\N<Naoto>Uh, you're, you're putting Miyaku's... in your mouth again...
\N<Naoto>It's... too slow... Isn't it too slow...

\N<Naoto>No way... It's just a joke, right...
\N<Kaede>So... what is the content of your worries?
\N<Kaede>Do you want to be cuckolded again...?
\N<Kaede>....I'm saying it's fine. It's not like it's the first time.
\N<Kaede>And being able to be with Naoto makes me happy too.
\N<Kaede>So, who's the other person? Don't tell me it's Yosuke-san?
\N<Kaede>Why are you staying silent...? I hope it's not someone weird.
\N<Naoto>Next... would going downhill be a bad idea...
\N<Kaede>Do you even understand what you're saying...?

\N<Kaede>Even though I should have wanted to erase the past that
caused Naoto so much pain...

\N<Naoto>But, even just imagining Kaede going downhill as my
partner...

\N<Kaede>Well, first of all, I haven't had any involvement with Naoto
since that incident.
\N<Naoto>Since that time... I haven't even seen her face...
\N<Kaede>So you haven't even apologized, have you?
\N<Kaede>Huh... That's not true! After what happened...
\N<Kaede>With someone like that... such a despicable person.
\N<Kaede>Sorry... let me think for a moment....

\N<Kaede>I never said it was okay. Being with such a despicable
person...
\N<Kaede>Yeah. I'll be back in the evening.
\N<Naoto>By now... I should go down the mountain...
\N<Kaede>Phew.... I might be a little tired today.
\N<Naoto>If, if I were to be squid...
\N<Naoto>Do you listen to what he says?
\N<Kaede>...It's because of our promise, after all.
\N<Naoto>No, this is impossible... waiting is impossible!!
\N<Naoto>W-What are you doing... W-Where are you...
\N<Kaede>Ah, welcome back! You were late, huh? Haha.
\N<Kaede>What's wrong? Did Miyani say something to you?
\N<Naoto>Um, can we go to the room for a moment?
\N<Kaede>Huh? Sure, but dinner is ready, you know?
\N<Kaede>Eat quickly, let's go to the field...!

\N<Naoto>Well, well, it can't be helped...! You must have been
tired...! Haha

\N<Yosuke>Ah, sorry for bothering you so early in the morning, Naoto-
kun and Kaede-chan.
\N<Naoto>What's going on? Why are you here so early in the morning?

\N<Yosuke>It seems like Naoto-kun is going to leave this village. So,
I thought we should all see him off, just in case.
\N<Naoto>Leaving this village...? Why all of a sudden?

\N<Yosuke>I think he said something like Because he finished what he
had to do and Because something shocking happened.

\N<Yosuke>Well then, everyone is gathering at the entrance of the
village!

\N<Naoto>I wonder what's going on, suddenly leaving the village like
this.
\N<Kaede>It's probably just another one of his whims, right?

\N<Naoto> He said it was because something shocking happened. Is it
because of Kaede? Haha.
\N<Kaede>If that's the reason, then he's an idiot.
\N<Naoto>Well then, let's go to the village!
\N<Naoto>Why... are you so late... huff... huff...!
\N<Naoto>You...you went down the mountain...down the mountain...!!!
\N<Shimoyama>Sorry for coming so late at night....
\N<Kaede>Naoto, I'm going to the back room....
\N<Shimoyama>I'm truly sorry for what I did in the past!!!
\N<Shimoyama>Ah, as I said, I was competing with Kaede-chan.
\N<Shimoyama>Ah, that's why I came here to kneel down as promised....
\N<Shimoyama>I just didn't want to apologize no matter what....

\N<Shimoyama>I'm really sorry about what happened back then! Please
forgive me...!!
\N<Naoto>W-Well... um... I guess I forgive you...
\N<Shimoyama>By the way, just out of curiosity...
\N<Shimoyama>I was so close... I was so close to making you come...!

\N<Shimoyama>If there's a next time...! If there's a next time, I can
make you come! Kaede-chan!!

\N<Shimoyama>Ah... Ah, so that's what it's about... There's no longer a
chance for you to listen to what I have to say.

\N<Shimoyama>Well, of course. I lost the bet. Just because I made you
come doesn't mean you can get away with being so selfish, right?

\N<Shimoyama>But! You're the first woman who hasn't done everything I
wanted as a man!

\N<Shimoyama>I want to challenge you one more time... Please! Just like
this!

\N<Shimoyama>You want to see it, right!? Kaede-chan trembling and
climaxing!! If we've come this far, even I want to see it...!
\N<Naoto>But! I need to confirm with Kaede first....

\N<Shimoyama>If Kaede-chan gives her approval, let me know and I'll be
waiting at my house tomorrow morning.

\N<Shimoyama>Naoto-kun... It's been quite some time, but... I'm truly
sorry.
\N<Naoto>Oh... speaking of which... what about today's footage!?
\N<Shimoyama>Oh, I can tell just by your voice....
\N<Shimoyama>Well, I ended up staying over today. Hmph!!
\N<Naoto>Don't mess with me! You broke our promise, didn't you!!
\N<Shimoyama>Well, that's how it is, you know....

\N<Shimoyama>I'll be leaving tomorrow morning, so take care. See you
later♡ Hmph....!!
